        text: "In 9th grade, studying at EMEF Plínio de Queiroz, a public school in Parque Boa Esperança, I discovered ISMART (Instituto Social para Motivar Apoiar e Reconhecer Talentos), an NGO that since 1999 has been seeking talented young people and offering full 100% scholarships for high school at top private schools for those who pass a rigorous selection process. /n After completing 5 stages — written tests in Portuguese, mathematics, and logic, an individual interview, a family interview, and a group work challenge throughout 2018 — I secured my spot at Colégio Objetivo on Avenida Paulista to attend high school.",
