        text: "During the exchange, I was accepted for a Software Engineering internship at BASF's global headquarters — the world's largest chemical company — in Ludwigshafen, Germany. /n My mission was to replace a legacy MatLab software used by the company's global R&D team — a heavy system, difficult to maintain, and dependent on expensive licenses. Working autonomously, I developed a modern web application in React/Vite for predictive calorimetry analysis, with no external dependencies, making the tool accessible to BASF engineers worldwide. /n The most impactful result was the performance optimization: I reduced chemical prediction processing time from 5 minutes to just 15 seconds — a 20x improvement. Beyond accelerating researchers' workflows, the new interface eliminated software license needs and democratized global access to the tool. /n This experience consolidated my ability to deliver high-impact solutions autonomously in a world-class corporate environment.",
